Lab Title:
CyberChef: The Basics

Platform/Provider:
TryHackMe

Date Completed:
6/23/26

Objectives:
Understand the purpose of CyberChef as a browser-based data transformation tool used for encoding, decoding, and basic analysis.
Practice using core CyberChef operations to convert data between common formats such as Base64, hexadecimal, and URL encoding.
Learn how to chain multiple operations into a recipe to process and reveal hidden or obfuscated data.

Summary of Activities:
Opened CyberChef and reviewed the interface, including the input pane, output pane, operations list, and recipe area.
Tested several basic transformations to observe how different encodings change the structure and readability of data.
Applied common decoding steps to recover plaintext from encoded samples.

Skills/Tools Used:
Browser, CyberChef web tool

Reflection:
This lab strengthened my understanding of CyberChef as a practical tool for data decoding, format conversion, and early-stage analysis. 
Working through the basics reinforced the importance of a structured, methodical approach when investigating unknown or obfuscated data. 
I also gained experience in reading results critically, chaining operations logically, and validating output instead of relying on assumptions.
